
What is Thread? 
    A thread is a smallest unit of execution inside a process.

java program = process

Why Threads? 
    Without threads multiple fuction will run one at a time or the task will get perform one at a time
    But , with treads it runs at same time 
    Due to which app becomes faster  scalable

üëâ Threads give concurrency(Multiple tasks making progress (time slicing)) :- Single Core CUP
üëâ Multi-core CPUs give parallelism:- Tasks run at same time :- Multi Core CPU eack core run task parallely

Java don‚Äôt run threads , it only creates threads
OS decides when to pause , when to restart 

THREAD CREATION
    1. Extends Thread class
    2. Implement Runnable interface ( Prefrred as it offers loose coupling , multiple inheritance)

1. Extends Thread class
Limitation:- No multiple inheritance

    public class MyThread extends Threads {
        static void run(){
            System.out.println("Thread is running...")
        }
    }


    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        Mythread t1 = new MyThread();
        t1.start();

        // You override run()
        // You call start(), not run()
        // start() ‚Üí creates a new thread
        // JVM internally calls run()
        //if we call run directly it behaves like a normal method.
    }

2. Implement Runnable interface
    class MyTask implements Runnable {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Task running");
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Thread t = new Thread(new MyTask());
        t.start();
    }
}



What is Thread Priority?
    It is the hint to OS scheduler to tell the priority of the thread
        Thread.MIN_PRIORITY  = 1
        Thread.NORM_PRIORITY = 5  // default
        Thread.MAX_PRIORITY  = 10

    Priority does not gurantee the execution order , it is only suggestion



What does sleep() do?
    Pauses the current thread for a given time.

    Key points:-

        sleep() is static
        Always affects the current running thread   

        Used for:
            delays
            retries
            simulations


What is Race Condition? 
    Race condition happens when multiple threads access or modify shared data at the same time 
    Shared data + multiple threads + no control = bug

        Key condition for race condition

            All three must be true:
                1Ô∏è Shared variable
                2Ô∏è Multiple threads  
                3Ô∏è At least one thread modifies data

        Remove any one ‚Üí no race condition.

Solution:-
1. Synchronized method

    synchronized void increment() {
        count++;
    }

2. Synchronized Block
        void increment() {
        synchronized(this) {
            //critical section
            count++;
        }
    }

What is ‚Äúcritical section‚Äù?

The part of code that accesses shared data and must not be executed by 
multiple threads simultaneously.


        NEW
        ‚Üì start()
        RUNNABLE
        ‚Üì waiting for lock
        BLOCKED
        ‚Üì gets lock
        RUNNABLE
        ‚Üì sleep()/wait()
        WAITING / TIMED_WAITING
        ‚Üì done
        TERMINATED

            One-line explanations (memorize)

            NEW ‚Üí thread created

            RUNNABLE ‚Üí ready or running

            BLOCKED ‚Üí waiting for lock

            WAITING ‚Üí waiting indefinitely

            TIMED_WAITING ‚Üí waiting for fixed time

            TERMINATED ‚Üí finished execution
